{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3ba98f5a-2f4a-49c9-9d71-605f16174489","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nNote: xUnit embeds the skip reason directly in `[Fact]`/`[Theory]` rather than using a separate attribute. All four frameworks will report skipped tests distinctly from passed/failed in test results.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"062ea0cc-2959-45eb-947e-6ecc9168c059","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without tools.","outputTokens":327,"requestId":"CFCA:131578:14D422F:1818E38:69EC136D"},"id":"d869de69-b30b-4d96-a9cc-b557204ceb5b","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:05:55.989Z","parentId":"2028a562-fd33-4046-9f39-59ce41b39bb0"}
